  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The aim of the study is to evaluate the efficacy of a wearable device using pulse
      electromagnetic fields on pain intensity reduction, measured by visual analogue score (VAS)
      and Western Ontario and McMaster Universities Osteoarthritis Index (WOMAC), in patients
      affected by osteoarthritis Secondary aim is the evaluate the effect on knee effusion
      reduction, when present and to evaluate pain intensity changes corrected by pain threshold
      measured by pressure algometry.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
