    <time_frame>baseline and 4 weeks</time_frame>
    <description>Multi-item questionnaire used to assess pain, stiffness, and physical function in patients with knee osteoarthritis.
The WOMAC consists of 24 items divided into 3 subscales:
Pain (5 items), Stiffness (2 items) and Physical Function (17 items). Score Range: On the Likert Scale version, the scores are summed for items in each subscale, with possible ranges as follows: pain=0-50, stiffness=0-20, physical function=0-170. A total WOMAC score is created by summing the items for all three subscales. A higher score represents a worse outcome.</description>
  </primary_outcome>
